HEADWORD: manned
<hw>manned</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a crew; -- of
vehicles; <as>as, a <ex>manned</ex> earth satellite was considered a
necessary research step; to minimize casualties, the military used
cruise missiles rather than <ex>manned</ex> aircraft for the
bombardment</as>. Opposite of <ant>unmanned</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
